headline: Tesla’s Price Target Is Rising Even as Its Profit Outlook Tanks
summary: “Tesla is truly unique in capital markets,” said Nicholas Colas, co-founder at DataTrek Research.  Over the past 12 months, the average forecast for Tesla’s 2026 net income has tumbled 56% from $14.1 billion to $6.1 billion.  The stock is up 7% in that time after closing Tuesday at $435.20, well above Wall Street’s expectations for a year from now.

headline: Texas Instruments (NASDAQ:TXN) Misses Q4 Analysts’ Revenue Estimates
summary: Analog chip manufacturer Texas Instruments (NASDAQ:TXN) fell short of the markets revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, but sales rose 10.4% year on year to $4.42 billion. On the other hand, next quarter’s outlook exceeded expectations with revenue guided to $4.5 billion at the midpoint, or 1.7% above analysts’ estimates. Its GAAP profit of $1.27 per share was 2.9% below analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Texas Instruments (TXN) Earnings Transcript
summary: Let me start with a quick overview of the fourth quarter.  The overall semiconductor market recovery is continuing, and we are well-positioned with inventory and capacity to meet immediate customer demand.  To better reflect the growth opportunities we see for our analog and embedded products, we reorganized our end markets to include data center, which includes sectors related to data center compute, data center networking, and rack power and thermal management.
